{%- comment -%}
  bd a7av.12 — Collection Quick Buy (native STKY replacement, web-team decision 2).

  A hover-to-reveal "Add to Cart" button overlaid on the lower edge of a product
  card image. SCOPED to collection pages only (request.page_type == 'collection')
  — the STKY app showed quick-buy on every page; the web team asked for
  collection-only.

  - Available (any product) → direct AJAX add of the first available variant via
    the shared [data-vrec-add] handler (assets/hairmnl-common.js → /cart/add.js →
    opens the drawer). Multi-variant products add the default variant too (strict
    STKY parity, web-team follow-up 2026-05-18); the shopper adjusts in the drawer.
  - Sold out → inert label.

  Hover-reveal is CSS (css-overrides.liquid §quick-buy): hidden on hover-capable
  devices until card hover; always visible on touch devices.

  Arg: product {Product} required.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if product != blank and request.page_type == 'collection' -%}
  {%- assign qb_variant = product.first_available_variant | default: product.variants.first -%}
  {%- if qb_variant -%}
    <div class="quick-buy" data-quick-buy>
      {%- comment -%} bd a7av.12 (web-team follow-up): direct-add the first available
          variant for ALL products, including multi-variant — strict STKY parity
          (STKY added the default variant from the grid). The shopper can adjust the
          variant in the drawer/cart that opens after add. {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if qb_variant.available -%}
        <button type="button"
                class="quick-buy__btn"
                data-vrec-add
                data-variant-id="{{ qb_variant.id }}"
                aria-label="{{ 'products.product.add_to_cart' | t | default: 'Add to cart' }}: {{ product.title | strip_html | escape }}">
          {{ 'products.product.add_to_cart' | t | default: 'Add to cart' }}
        </button>
      {%- else -%}
        <span class="quick-buy__btn quick-buy__btn--soldout" aria-disabled="true">
          {{ 'products.product.sold_out' | t | default: 'Sold out' }}
        </span>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
